The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | France make Cup final with 3-0 victory
                                                                                                                       7                                      France make Cup final with 3-0 victory
                      
	Lyon: France reached their first Davis Cup final in eight years after securing an insurmountable 3-0 lead over Argentina by winning the doubles on Saturday.         
	Michael Llodra and Arnaud Clement, playing together in Davis Cup for the first time in more than two years, defeated Eduardo Schwank and Horacio Zeballos 6-4, 7-5, 6-3 in two and a half hours to decide the best-of-five tie.         
	In Belgrade, the Czech Republic took a 2-1 lead over Serbia in their semi-final by winning Saturdays doubles despite the return of second-ranked Novak Djokovic for Serbia.         
	Tomas Berdych and Radek Stepanek rallied to defeat Djokovic and Nenad Zimonjic 3-6, 6-1, 6-4, 6-1.         
	France won the last of their nine Davis Cup titles in 2001 and lost to Russia at home in the 2002 final.         
	All of the French players enjoyed a lap of honour in the indoor hard-court of the Palais des Sports and were joined in their celebrations by replacement Richard Gasquet, injured Jo-Wilfried Tsonga and Julien Benneteau.         
	Im so proud, they are here, all together. All those seven guys were key elements in our successes, France captain Guy Forget said. But there is another tie to play, we have such a talented team, and we cant be satisfied with the runners-up place.On Friday, Llodra put France ahead with a 7-5, 4-6, 7-5, 6-3 win over Juan Monaco then Gael Monfils topped David Nalbandian 6-4, 2-6, 6-4, 6-3. (agencies)                                                                                                                     
